   <concept id="DAFFARS_5316_505" class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
      <title class="- topic/title "> 
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">5316.505</ph> Ordering</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p outputclass="List1" class="- topic/p ">(b) <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Orders under multiple award contracts</i>.</p>
         <p outputclass="List2" class="- topic/p ">(1) <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Fair opportunity</i>.</p>
         <p outputclass="List3" class="- topic/p ">(ii) The contracting officer must use streamlined ordering procedures. SCOs must justify the use of <xref format="html"
                  href="https://www.acquisition.gov/far/part-15#FAR_Subpart_15_3"
                  scope="external"
                  class="- topic/xref ">FAR 15.3</xref> Source Selection Procedures for any contract or task-order or delivery-order, regardless of dollar value made in accordance with <xref format="html"
                  href="https://www.acquisition.gov/far/part-16#FAR_16_505"
                  scope="external"
                  class="- topic/xref ">FAR 16.505</xref>. The SCO must submit justifications to the <xref format="html"
                  href="https://www.acquisition.gov/daffars/part-5302-definitions-words-and-terms"
                  scope="external"
                  class="- topic/xref ">cognizant HCA Workflow</xref> before proceeding with the source selection and/or Clearance session.</p>
         <p outputclass="List2" rev="Revised June 12, 2024" class="- topic/p ">(2) <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Exceptions to the fair opportunity process</i>.</p>
         <p outputclass="List3" rev="Revised June 12, 2024" class="- topic/p ">(ii) See the tailorable <xref href="https://usaf.dps.mil/sites/AFCC/AQCP/KnowledgeCenter/SitePages/DAFFARS-Templates.aspx"
                  format="html"
                  scope="external"
                  class="- topic/xref ">Justification for an Exception to Fair Opportunity</xref> template. </p>
         <p outputclass="List4" rev="Revised June 12, 2024" class="- topic/p ">(C) <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Approval.</i> For all exceptions to fair opportunity, follow guidance in <xref href="https://www.acquisition.gov/daffars/part-5306-competition-requirements#DAFFARS_5306_304"
                  format="html"
                  scope="external"
                  class="- topic/xref ">DAFFARS5306.304</xref>. For those meeting the definition of a bridge action at <xref href="https://www.acquisition.gov/daffars/part-5302-definitions-words-and-terms"
                  format="html"
                  scope="external"
                  class="- topic/xref ">DAFFARS 5302.101</xref>, also follow <xref href="https://www.acquisition.gov/daffars/part-5306-competition-requirements#DAFFARS_5306_303_1_90"
                  format="html"
                  scope="external"
                  class="- topic/xref ">DAFFARS 5306.303-1-90</xref>. </p>
         <p outputclass="List5" rev="Revised June 12, 2024" class="- topic/p ">(<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">4</i>) See <xref href="https://www.acquisition.gov/daffars/mp5301-federal-acquisition-regulations-system#DAFFARS_MP5301_601"
                  format="html"
                  scope="external"
                  class="- topic/xref ">MP5301.601(a)(i)</xref>.</p>
         <p outputclass="List2" rev="Revised June 12, 2024" class="- topic/p ">(7) <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Decision documentation for orders</i>. Unless designated otherwise by the acquisition approving authority, SADA, or SCO, the contracting officer has decision making authority.</p>
         <p outputclass="List2" class="- topic/p ">(8) <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Task-order and delivery-order ombudsman</i>. See <xref format="html"
                  href="https://www.acquisition.gov/daffars/part-5301-federal-acquisition-regulations-system#DAFFARS_SUBPART_5301_91"
                  scope="external"
                  class="- topic/xref ">DAFFARS 5301.91</xref>.<ph id="Toc351650167" class="- topic/ph "/> 
         </p>
      </conbody>
